d leisure culture within public spaces in order to analyze how teens like China are marginalized and policed as they attempt to carve out places for themselves within New York’s contested terrains.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfrican American girlsxBrooklyn (New York, N.Y.). 0aAfrican American girlszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aConsumer behaviorxBrooklyn (New York, N.Y.)xNew York (State)xNew YorkxBrooklyn. 0aConsumer behaviorzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aMinority youthxBrooklyn (New York, N.Y.). 0aMinority youthzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aWest IndiansxSocial life and customsxBrooklyn (New York, N.Y.). 0aWest IndianszNew York (State)zNew YorkxSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081475247040uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814752470.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814765289423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814765289/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK